Html:
I read the Documentation about &quot;How to use a custom color palette&quot;, but I'm having problems with this.<br />
<br />
My code is like this:<br />
<br />
On MainPage.xaml:<br />
<pre><code>&lt;chart:DoughnutChart
                        ...
                       Palette=&quot;{StaticResource CustomColors}&quot;
                        ... &gt;

                        &lt;chart:DoughnutChart.Series&gt;
                        ...
                        &lt;/chart:DoughnutChart.Series&gt;
&lt;/chart:DoughnutChart&gt;</code></pre>

On Generic.xaml:<br />
<pre><code>&lt;ResourceDictionary
    xmlns=&quot;http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation&quot; 
    xmlns:x=&quot;http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml&quot;
    xmlns:chart=&quot;clr-namespace:De.TorstenMandelkow.MetroChart&quot;&gt;

    &lt;chart:ResourceDictionaryCollection x:Key=&quot;CustomColors&quot;&gt;
        &lt;ResourceDictionary&gt;
            &lt;SolidColorBrush x:Key=&quot;Brush1&quot; Color=&quot;#FF5B9BD5&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;/ResourceDictionary&gt;
        &lt;ResourceDictionary&gt;
            &lt;SolidColorBrush x:Key=&quot;Brush2&quot; Color=&quot;#FFED7D31&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;/ResourceDictionary&gt;
        &lt;ResourceDictionary&gt;
            &lt;SolidColorBrush x:Key=&quot;Brush3&quot; Color=&quot;#FFA5A5A5&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;/ResourceDictionary&gt;
        &lt;ResourceDictionary&gt;
            &lt;SolidColorBrush x:Key=&quot;Brush4&quot; Color=&quot;#FFFFC000&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;/ResourceDictionary&gt;
    &lt;/chart:ResourceDictionaryCollection&gt;
&lt;/ResourceDictionary&gt;</code></pre>

But &quot;Palette=&quot;{StaticResource CustomColors}&quot; is not recognized.<br />
The phrase &quot;The resource 'CustomColors' could not be resolver&quot; appears.<br />
<br />
Has anyone had this problem? There is another way to change the colors?<br />
